    "description": "rumMGE is a database containing over 1.2 million mobile genetic elements (MGEs) identified from 2,458 ruminant gastrointestinal metagenomic samples. The resource integrates host, animal, and geographic information for these MGEs, facilitating research into microbial adaptation and functional responses to dietary changes.",
